        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You've always enjoyed pretending to be someone else.  Sometimes it was because you just didn't want to be you.  Other times it was for the praise you got for your skills.  In high school, drama nerds were your people, and they encouraged you to go to college to become a more well-rounded actor.  Plus, auditions were hard, and college was bound to help, even if your student loans would be brutal by the time you were done.  You joined Theta Heta because you enjoyed the role you played around your brothers and sisters, but you never really had the Greek spirit.  You were the first to try to run when that pack swept in and swept everyone up in that shovelheading party.  You play the part of the dutiful Sabbat member, but your heart isn't in it.  You've only stayed so far for two reasons:  The vinculum has a grip on you, and you don't have a plan for what you'd do next.  You're pretty sure that an acting career isn't an option any more."
